# Perl
# What is Perl?
Perl (Practical Extraction and Reporting Language) is a high-level, interpreted, dynamically typed scripting language developed by Larry Wall in 1987. It was originally designed for text processing and report generation but later evolved into a powerful general-purpose programming language.

# key Features of perl**
-Interpreted language (no separate compilation required)
-Dynamically typed (no need to declare data types)
-Strong text and pattern matching capabilities
-Cross-platform (Linux, Windows, macOS)
-Automatic memory management
-Supports procedural and functional programming styles
-Rich library support (CPAN – Comprehensive Perl Archive Network)

